  "grammar_rule": {
    "metadata": {
      "id": "verb_to_be_a1",
      "title": "Verb To Be",
      "level": "A1",
      "topic": "Greetings & Personal Information",
      "topic_arabic": "التحيات والمعلومات الشخصية",
      "category": "grammar",
      "subcategory": "verbs",
      "estimated_minutes": 45,
      "difficulty": 1,
      "tags": [
        "verb to be",
        "am",
        "is",
        "are",
        "greetings",
        "personal info",
        "present simple"
      ]
    },
    "explanation": {
      "short": "The verb \"to be\" is the most fundamental verb in English. It describes states, identities, and characteristics.",
      "short_arabic": "فعل \"يكون\" هو أهم فعل في اللغة الإنجليزية. يصف الحالات والهويات والصفات.",
      "detailed": "The verb \"to be\" (am/is/are) is used to talk about names, ages, nationalities, occupations, feelings, and locations. It connects the subject to a complement (noun, adjective, or prepositional phrase).",
      "detailed_arabic": "يستخدم فعل \"يكون\" (am/is/are) للحديث عن الأسماء والأعمار والجنسيات والمهن والمشاعر والأماكن. يربط الفاعل بالمتمم (اسم أو صفة أو شبه جملة).",
      "key_points": [
        {
          "point": "The verb \"to be\" changes form depending on the subject",
          "arabic": "يتغير شكل فعل \"يكون\" حسب الفاعل"
        },
        {
          "point": "I always uses \"am\"",
          "arabic": "I تأتي دائماً مع am"
        },
        {
          "point": "He/She/It always use \"is\"",
          "arabic": "He/She/It تأتي مع is"
        },
        {
          "point": "You/We/They always use \"are\"",
          "arabic": "You/We/They تأتي مع are"
        },
        {
          "point": "Contractions (short forms) are very common in spoken English",
          "arabic": "الاختصارات شائعة جداً في الإنجليزية المحكية"
        }
      ],
      "usage_context": {
        "formal": "Full forms are preferred in academic writing and formal documents: \"I am a student.\"",
        "informal": "Contracted forms are used in everyday conversation: \"I'm a student.\"",
        "written": "Both forms are acceptable in writing; contractions are less common in very formal texts."
      }
    },
